# sw-git-conventions

**Authoritative reference:** `skills/git-workflow/SKILL.md`. This rule encodes enforceable guardrails only.

## Branch names

- Pattern: `<type>/<slug>` or `docs/<topic>` where `type` ‚àà `release-please-config.json` changelog types.
- Enforced by `scripts/branch-name-guard.py` at worktree/branch creation (`scripts/worktree_lib.py` for Python).
- `pf/<name>` is prohibited. Fail closed on non-conforming names.

## Commit messages

- Conventional Commits: `type(scope): description` or `type!: description` for breaking changes.
- Types single-sourced from `release-please-config.json`.
- Enforced by `scripts/commit-msg-guard.py` via `core/hooks/commit-msg`.

## PR / merge bodies

- Templates: `core/sw-reference/templates/pr-body.md`, `merge-commit.md`.
- Required fields validated by `scripts/git_template_lib.py`; host `pr-create` fails closed on missing fields.

## Documentation authoring

- Brainstorm/PRD/doc pipeline work occurs on `docs/<topic>` in a dedicated worktree (`scripts/docs_worktree.py`).
- Never create local commits on the protected default branch for doc authoring.
- Docs reach trunk via `scripts/docs_pr.py` (docs-only PR), not direct push.
- Feature-branch `spec-seed` (PRD 013) remains for implementation handoff; docs durability is separate (R32).



## Two-track doc edits (PRD 035 R10‚ÄìR14)

- **Mechanical** ‚Äî reconciler-generated artifacts only (INDEX `derived` region, SUPERSEDED manifest, gap index):
  batched via `scripts/docs-merge.py` with CI-gated auto-merge or direct-to-trunk when protection probe permits.
  Under issue-store `separate-project` (PRD 057 R1‚ÄìR3) the mechanical allowlist **projects to the authoritative
  store** instead ‚Äî gap capture write-through (R1), spec-seed skips the local INDEX write (R2), and
  `reconcile_core` skips tracked `INDEX.md`/`INDEX-archive.md`/`SUPERSEDED.md`/legacy-projection writes and
  projects the derived map to the store or a gitignored cache (R3). `same-repo` retains local mechanical writes
  unchanged.
- **Substantive** ‚Äî any path under `docs/planning/<unit-id>/` (body or frontmatter): auto-driven docs worktree +
  PR via `scripts/docs-edit-route.py route-substantive` ‚Üí `docs_worktree.py` / `docs_pr.py`.
- **`inFlight` region** ‚Äî never mechanically edited (PRD 032 deliver writer sole region).
- Branch protection is detected via host API; ambiguous/missing auth fails closed to the PR path ‚Äî never bypass
  the protected trunk merge gate.

